text: Everquest is blocked by the University firewall
The UC Davis network is continually scanned for prohibited activities and network threats.
Sony Playstation 2 is allowed by the University firewall
POP3 and secure POP are allowed by the University firewall
ACT/IT Infrastructure monitors traffic on the network for the purpose of maintaining proper network function
University Housing monitors only the amount of traffic
Quotas for students are 5000 Megabyte per hr download and 2000 Megabyte per hr upload
CounterStrike server is blocked by the University firewall
HTTP and HTTPS are allowed by the University firewall

If a student is in obvious violations of copyright law by using a room's wired connection (ie ResNet) to distribute copyrighted materials, the room's connection will be disabled, and the issue could be sent to Housing Student Judicial Affairs
Telnet is allowed by the University firewall
There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
